{"word":"οἰκτίζω","slug":"οἰκτίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἰκτίζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:οἶκτος'><el>οἶκτος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to pity, have pity upon</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:— <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> in same sense, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> also, <i>to bewail, lament</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to express one's pity</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>οἶκτον οἰκτίζεσθαι</el> <i>to utter a wail</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}